  <section id="reward-chart-bribe">
    <h2>Reward chart or bribe: what is the difference?</h2>
    <p>Many parents worry that reward charts are just bribes. The difference is timing.</p>
    <p>A bribe usually happens after things have already gone wrong. For example: &ldquo;Please stop screaming and I&rsquo;ll give you candy.&rdquo;</p>
    <p>A reward chart is agreed before the routine starts. For example: &ldquo;When you finish your bedtime steps with a calm body, you earn one sticker. When the path is full, we have a family movie night.&rdquo;</p>
    <p>A bribe teaches a child that big resistance can create a better deal. A reward chart teaches a child that practice leads to progress. That is why the plan should be explained while the child is calm, not negotiated in the middle of the hardest moment.</p>
