  <section id="reward-chart-fade">
    <h2>How long should you use a reward chart?</h2>
    <p>Use the chart long enough for the behavior to become easier, then slowly fade it. A reward chart is like training wheels. It is helpful while your child is learning, but the goal is not to use it forever.</p>
    <p>When your child is succeeding often, you can:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Move from a sticker for every step to a sticker for a full routine.</li>
      <li>Move from daily rewards to weekly rewards.</li>
      <li>Keep the praise but reduce the physical rewards.</li>
      <li>Replace the chart with a simple checklist.</li>
      <li>Celebrate that the habit is becoming &ldquo;just what we do.&rdquo;</li>
    </ul>
    <p>You can say: &ldquo;You have learned this so well that we do not need a sticker every time anymore. I&rsquo;m proud of how independent you are becoming.&rdquo;</p>
